{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-post-js","path":"/create-zfs-raid-10-array-napp","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"html":"<p><a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Nested_RAID_levels#RAID_1.2B0\">RAID 10</a> is great as a highly reliable storage array for your personal files. The <a href=\"https://docs.oracle.com/cd/E19253-01/819-5461/zfsover-2/\">ZFS file-system</a> is capable of protecting your data against corruption, but not against hardware failures. ZFS however implements <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Non-standard_RAID_levels#RAID-Z\">RAID-Z</a> (RAID 5, 6 and 7) to ensure redundancy across multiple drives. RAID 10 (1+0 or mirror + stripe) is not offered as a choice in ZFS but can be easily done manually for a similar effect. This guide will be focused on <a href=\"http://www.napp-it.org/index_en.html\">nappit</a> but can be modified for whichever ZFS platform you are using.</p>\n<!-- more -->\n<h2 id=\"create-the-array-pool\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#create-the-array-pool\" aria-label=\"create the array pool permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Create the Array (Pool)</h2>\n<p><strong>1.</strong> Create a new pool with the first two disks to be mirrored.</p>\n<p><em>Select the 'Create Pool' option from the Pools dropdown</em>:</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 409px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/75a0343f0e8e76ace74c30c3140aa654/ff023/11.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 110.7981220657277%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"create a new pool\"\n        title=\"create a new pool\"\n        src=\"/static/75a0343f0e8e76ace74c30c3140aa654/ff023/11.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/75a0343f0e8e76ace74c30c3140aa654/53f68/11.png 213w,\n/static/75a0343f0e8e76ace74c30c3140aa654/ff023/11.png 409w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 409px) 100vw, 409px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p><strong>2.</strong> Enter the pool details and select the first mirror.</p>\n<p><em>Select the first mirror of the RAID 10 array</em>:</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 676px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/49acd244088119552e07cb15d81e44e0/ff08e/21.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 53.990610328638496%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"first mirrored pair for raid 10\"\n        title=\"first mirrored pair for raid 10\"\n        src=\"/static/49acd244088119552e07cb15d81e44e0/ff08e/21.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/49acd244088119552e07cb15d81e44e0/53f68/21.png 213w,\n/static/49acd244088119552e07cb15d81e44e0/df70d/21.png 425w,\n/static/49acd244088119552e07cb15d81e44e0/ff08e/21.png 676w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 676px) 100vw, 676px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p><strong>3.</strong> Extend the new pool by selecting the option from the menu.</p>\n<p><em>Back in the dropdown menu, select the option to 'Extend Pool'</em>:</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 665px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/b4e4512e41610cf8f07d7fba43bb7e4b/a300e/31.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 74.17840375586854%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"extend the pool\"\n        title=\"extend the pool\"\n        src=\"/static/b4e4512e41610cf8f07d7fba43bb7e4b/a300e/31.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/b4e4512e41610cf8f07d7fba43bb7e4b/53f68/31.png 213w,\n/static/b4e4512e41610cf8f07d7fba43bb7e4b/df70d/31.png 425w,\n/static/b4e4512e41610cf8f07d7fba43bb7e4b/a300e/31.png 665w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 665px) 100vw, 665px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p><strong>4.</strong> Select the next two disks to be in the pool and set the option to mirror.</p>\n<p><em>Select the next mirror to be part of the RAID 10 array</em>:</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 670px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/9df5569c9338987c441839751443461e/6bbca/41.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 38.967136150234744%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"add any mirrors to raid 10 array\"\n        title=\"add any mirrors to raid 10 array\"\n        src=\"/static/9df5569c9338987c441839751443461e/6bbca/41.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/9df5569c9338987c441839751443461e/53f68/41.png 213w,\n/static/9df5569c9338987c441839751443461e/df70d/41.png 425w,\n/static/9df5569c9338987c441839751443461e/6bbca/41.png 670w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 670px) 100vw, 670px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p><strong>5.</strong> Select any remaining disks to be in the pool and also set the option to mirror.</p>\n<p><em>Optionally, select any remaining mirrors and repeat this step if necessary if you have more disks remaining.</em>:</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 652px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/e0c94888df48b8877c44517ddccba6ec/43b96/5.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 34.27230046948357%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"add last drives to raid 10 array\"\n        title=\"add last drives to raid 10 array\"\n        src=\"/static/e0c94888df48b8877c44517ddccba6ec/43b96/5.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/e0c94888df48b8877c44517ddccba6ec/53f68/5.png 213w,\n/static/e0c94888df48b8877c44517ddccba6ec/df70d/5.png 425w,\n/static/e0c94888df48b8877c44517ddccba6ec/43b96/5.png 652w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 652px) 100vw, 652px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<h2 id=\"verify-the-raid-10-array\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#verify-the-raid-10-array\" aria-label=\"verify the raid 10 array permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Verify the RAID 10 Array</h2>\n<p>If successful, in the main page of the your 'Pools', nappit will list your new RAID 10 array. Alternatively, run the command 'zpool status' to return the Pools and their allocated drives within the terminal.</p>\n<p><em>RAID 10 created. Mirrors in a stripe.</em>:</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 600px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/4e20fc7e17f3662bceeefd0d97a05b74/dface/6.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 76.52582159624413%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"raid 10 complete\"\n        title=\"raid 10 complete\"\n        src=\"/static/4e20fc7e17f3662bceeefd0d97a05b74/dface/6.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/4e20fc7e17f3662bceeefd0d97a05b74/53f68/6.png 213w,\n/static/4e20fc7e17f3662bceeefd0d97a05b74/df70d/6.png 425w,\n/static/4e20fc7e17f3662bceeefd0d97a05b74/dface/6.png 600w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<h2 id=\"my-thoughts-of-raid-10\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#my-thoughts-of-raid-10\" aria-label=\"my thoughts of raid 10 permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>My thoughts of RAID 10</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>I just lost 12TB of space just from doing this. RAID 10 and any mirrored level of RAID will take half of your disk space for redundancy.</li>\n<li>I like the idea that half your drives can die but the system would still be up, given <em>the right ones</em> die. The possibility of that are slim but good if you are using a lot of drives (more than just 6).</li>\n<li>RAID 10 increases your read speeds as more mirrors are added as all the drives perform the same read task. Reading and writing speeds were still limited to my network connection and I did not see any performance difference with RAID-Z2 (RAID 6) - which I eventually changed to.</li>\n<li>Upgrading drives, adding and removing mirrors is easier than RAID-Z</li>\n</ul>","timeToRead":3,"excerpt":"RAID 10 is great as a highly reliable storage array for your personal files. The ZFS file-system is capable of protecting your data against…","fileAbsolutePath":"/home/runner/work/calvin.me/calvin.me/master/posts/2014/2014-09-04-create-zfs-raid-10-array-napp/index.md","frontmatter":{"title":"How To Create a ZFS RAID 10 Array","categories":["Storage"],"tags":["napp-it","RAID","zfs"],"thumbnail":{"childImageSharp":{"gatsbyImageData":{"layout":"fixed","backgroundColor":"#080808","images":{"fallback":{"src":"/static/2db81c7616398f5d07dfdf173ca994ab/ccc8a/thumbnail.png","srcSet":"/static/2db81c7616398f5d07dfdf173ca994ab/ccc8a/thumbnail.png 150w,\n/static/2db81c7616398f5d07dfdf173ca994ab/67d4a/thumbnail.png 300w","sizes":"150px"},"sources":[{"srcSet":"/static/2db81c7616398f5d07dfdf173ca994ab/3554d/thumbnail.webp 150w,\n/static/2db81c7616398f5d07dfdf173ca994ab/c437f/thumbnail.webp 300w","type":"image/webp","sizes":"150px"}]},"width":150,"height":150}}}}}},"pageContext":{"filter":"/^.*\\/\\d{4}-\\d{2}-\\d{2}-create-zfs-raid-10-array-napp\\/.*$/"}},"staticQueryHashes":[]}